commentary: Rabada to Porterfield, OUT too quick again, coming back in towards off stump, did that flick the pad on its way through? Radaba thought so... and so did Joel Wilson! The finger went up after a moment's consideration, and Porterfield decides to review... Time for DRS (though this isn't really a test of the new system, since it only needed to be clipping either way), the ball was pitching in line, point of impact umpire's call... and clipping the top corner of off stump! It's about as close as it gets but there'll be no reprieve, Rabada striking second ball
